<item>
            <title>[GROOVY-7789] ClosureParams type inference compilation error when wrapping closure with object</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/GROOVY-7789</link>
                <project id="12318123" key="GROOVY">Groovy</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;The following code does not compile:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.*
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;import&lt;/span&gt; groovy.transform.stc.*

@CompileStatic
&lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;Test {

    &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;class &lt;/span&gt;A&amp;lt;IN&amp;gt; {
        Closure c

        A(@ClosureParams(value = FromString, options = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;IN&apos;&lt;/span&gt;) Closure c) {
            &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;this&lt;/span&gt;.c = c
        }

        void call(IN param) {
            c.call(param)
        }
    }

    def &amp;lt;IN&amp;gt; A wrap(@ClosureParams(value = FromString, options = &lt;span class=&quot;code-quote&quot;&gt;&apos;IN&apos;&lt;/span&gt;) Closure c) {
        &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;new&lt;/span&gt; A&amp;lt;IN&amp;gt;(c)
    }

    def test() {
        (wrap { i -&amp;gt; i.size() }).call([])
    }

}
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Compilation error:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;div class=&quot;code panel&quot; style=&quot;border-width: 1px;&quot;&gt;&lt;div class=&quot;codeContent panelContent&quot;&gt;
&lt;pre class=&quot;code-java&quot;&gt;org.codehaus.groovy.control.MultipleCompilationErrorsException: startup failed:
/tmp/groovy-2.4.6/test.groovy: 25: [Static type checking] - Cannot find matching method java.lang.&lt;span class=&quot;code-object&quot;&gt;Object&lt;/span&gt;#size(). Please check &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the declared type is right and &lt;span class=&quot;code-keyword&quot;&gt;if&lt;/span&gt; the method exists.
 @ line 24, column 22.
           (wrap { i -&amp;gt; i.size() }).call([])
&lt;/pre&gt;
&lt;/div&gt;&lt;/div&gt;

&lt;p&gt;I&apos;d expect &apos;i&apos; being infered as java.util.List&lt;br/&gt;
Explicit this.&amp;lt;List&amp;gt;wrap does not help neither&lt;/p&gt;</description>
